  "text": "The author is pleased to thank Martin Bridson for his suggestion that the methods of this paper might be applied in the context of general combability conditions. The finite presentability claim of Theorem 2 has been proved by Bridson in [CITATION_1] . The n! upper bound on the Dehn function is an improvement on that in [CITATION_2] , although one should note that in [CITATION_3] Bridson is working in the more general context of combings in which the combing lines σ g are not required to be geodesics.",
